---
title: Antigone's Grilled Aubergine and Lamb Papoutsakia with Toasted Tomato Bulgur
description: The Greek word papoutsakia translates to 'little shoes' which is said to reference the appearance of the aubergine. Papoutsakia is a popular dish, consisting of halved aubergine boiled or roasted, its centre scooped out and filled with meats, vegetables and even eggs, topped with béchamel sauce and grilled. The addition of béchamel is usually traced to Nikolaos Tselemendes, a chef from the island of Sifnos thought to be responsible for French influences on Greek cuisine.
